  "why": "The paper's mutation mechanism produces full reconstructed images via an adversarial example generator (AEG / CycleGAN) and treats those reconstructed images as adversarial inputs that are stored and used to retrain and test models. That is, the fuzzer generates complete image examples (rendered/reconstructed images) rather than tiny in-memory floating-point perturbations applied only in a normalized representation. Because the generated adversarial examples are actual image artifacts placed into the processing pool and added to training/test sets, they are inherently stable with respect to standard serialization (i.e., they are generated as images and used as dataset entries), so failure-inducing perturbations are not likely to be lost by later clipping/rounding during save/load.",
